  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I Recover deleted contacts from a Nokia phone?",
  "response": "Recovering deleted contacts from a Nokia phone depends on the model and operating system (e.g., Symbian, Series 30+, or Android). Here are some general methods you can try:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Check Cloud Backup (if applicable)**  \nIf your Nokia phone is a modern Android-based model (e.g., Nokia 6, 7, or 8) and you\u2019ve synced your contacts with Google, you can restore them from your Google account.  \n- Go to your phone\u2019s **Settings** > **Accounts** > **Google**.  \n- Ensure **Contacts** sync is enabled.  \n- Open the **Contacts** app and check if your deleted contacts reappear.  \n- If not, you can restore contacts from Google\u2019s backup:  \n  - Visit [Google Contacts](https://contacts.google.com).  \n  - Click **Settings** > **Undo Changes** and choose the time range to restore contacts.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Restore from Nokia Suite or PC Suite (Older Nokia Phones)**  \nFor older Nokia phones running Symbian or Series 30+, use Nokia Suite or Nokia PC Suite if you\u2019ve previously backed up your contacts to your computer.  \n- Connect your phone to your PC via USB.  \n- Open Nokia Suite/PC Suite.  \n- Look for the **Backup & Restore** option and restore your contacts from the backup file.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Check SIM Card**  \nIf your contacts were saved to your SIM card, they might still be there.  \n- Insert the SIM card into another phone and check if the contacts are accessible.  \n- If yes, copy them back to your Nokia phone.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Use Third-Party Recovery Software (Android-Based Nokia Phones)**  \nFor Nokia Android phones, you can use third-party recovery apps like **Dr.Fone**, **DiskDigger**, or **EaseUS MobiSaver** to recover deleted contacts.  \n- Install the app on your PC or phone.  \n- Connect your phone to your PC (if required).  \n- Follow the app\u2019s instructions to scan for and recover deleted contacts.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Check Local Backup**  \nIf your Nokia phone has a local backup feature, check if you\u2019ve previously backed up your contacts.  \n- Go to **Settings** > **System** > **Backup** (or similar).  \n- Restore the backup file if available.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Contact Nokia Support**  \nIf none of the above methods work, reach out to Nokia\u2019s customer support for further assistance.\n\n---\n\n**Important Note:** Avoid adding new data to your phone after deleting contacts, as this can overwrite the deleted data and make recovery more difficult.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
